cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY. 

This paper deals with the problem of robots interacting with liquids, which is a common manipulation task in robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also uses fully convolutional neural networks to detect and track liquids, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of neural networks also suggests the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with the integration of temporal information, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
